Following the death of one of its staff from Covid-19 in Kano at the weekend, First Bank Nigeria has reiterated its commitment to protecting the health and safety of all staff, customers and host communities in the fight against the spread of Coronavirus. The bank in a statement issued at the weekend, noted that it has put measures in place to ensure that the deadly virus does not pose a threat to its staff, customers and host communities. Abdullahi Lawal, who worked in the main branch of the bank in Kano had died from the virus at the weekend. Announcing, his death, the FBN in a statement said “our thoughts and prayers are with his family at this time as we do all that is necessary to support them. We ask that all necessary courtesies be extended to the family so they can grieve privately. “As a responsible corporate organisation, FirstBank has been at the fore-front of the concerted efforts against the coronavirus pandemic alongside others. “We have robust protocols in place including practicing social distancing, frequently disinfecting our buildings and locations even whilst ensuring services are available through our alternative channels such as our ATMs and other digital platforms.